title: async: Corrected filter and reject definitions.
body:
**Summary**
Corrected definitions for series, parallel, filter, reject, their aliases and related functions.

**Details**
The iterator from my previous commit #5518 was incorrectly typed. It should be an `AsyncBooleanIterator<T>` similar to the detect API.

The series and parallel function callbacks incorrectly required an Error as a first argument.

This change affects: series, parallel, parallelLimit, filter, filterSeries, filterLimit, select, selectSeries, selectLimit, reject, rejectSeries, rejectLimit.

I have also added my name to the definition credits.

**References**
https://github.com/caolan/async#filter
https://github.com/caolan/async#reject
https://github.com/caolan/async#detect
https://github.com/caolan/async#series
https://github.com/caolan/async#parallel

title: Update XRegExp to 3.0.0
body:
This updates the definitions for XRegExp to the recently released version 3.0.0.

I tried all kinds of things (classes with static methods, interfaces, etc) to **not** duplicate the function definitions, but to no avail. I had to duplicate them because XRegExp can now be used in two ways:

```
import X = require('xregexp');
X();
```

or via

```
import XRegExp = X.XRegExp;
XRegExp()
```

I found no other way to solve this in TypeScript. If we can DRY this up somehow, please let me know how :)
